At the same time, he has personally criticized the idea of Bush to send reinforcements in an Iraq consumed by the civil war as "irresponsible and a decision in its consequences." "
The following month, however, have shown that the strategy of Bush, who came from the recommendations of the commanders of campaigns, was the only possible and likely to point that the newspapers currently do not speak at all of Iraq.
This has not enhanced the reputation of Bush, however, objectively speaking, it was left to his successor a final situation much more favourable than we could have hoped.
