The announcement of the arrest was first reported by the New York Times, on Friday evening.
The new US policy insists that the Cuban government by concrete steps, such as releasing political prisoners and create more space for the opposition, so that the to reciprocate..
Mobile phones and laptops are permitted to Cuba, although consumer goods and in a country or the average salary of an employee is $15 per month. per month.
Only this year, the Cuban government has granted to ordinary citizens the right to buy mobile phones; they are mainly used for text messages or for a conversation which corresponds to a day's pay.
On the island, the use of the Internet is extremely limited.
It is available in luxury hotels and for foreign visitors in the country, as well as in some government buildings, such as universities.
Cubans who want to connect often must provide their name to the government.
Access to many Web sites is restricted..
The detention of an American in Cuba is rare.
Most of the few in Cuba are behind bars for crimes such as drug trafficking, "says Gloria Berbena, press officer with the U.S. Interests Section in Havana.
Berbena said that she could not provide more information on the arrest.
The arrest and detention are a big mistake.
An activity that, in any open society, would be allowed - free mobile phones - is a crime in Cuba, "said Jose Miguel Vivanco, Americas program director of the group Human Rights Watch, which has recently published a report on freedoms in Cuba, called" New Castro, Cuba ", referring to the installation of Raul Castro as leader of the country to replace Fidel, his older brother.
According to Vivanco, an accused is often arrested, put on trial and jailed on the same day..
He said that any solution would probably be policy and that the Cuban government often causes a negative reaction in the United States, when the two countries begin to initiate a dialogue.
