There are hallucinations or delusions when the balance, of neurotransmettrices in the brain - dopamine, norepinephrine, serotonin and the achétylcholine - breaks down and that the interaction between the different parts of the brain is disrupted.
and delusional thoughts occur very often during a schizophrenic psychosis..
The force of attraction has more power on the person.
Since antiquity, philosophers and doctors have always looked at the relationship between the madness and the dream.
For Aristotle, hallucinations were a form of rêve-éveillé; Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of modern psychiatry, found in 1861 "a great similarity between the madness and the dream," Sigmund Freud the dream was "a psychosis with all irregularities, imagination, and sensory illusions and". "
