75% of working mothers have had problems because of their maternity
at work has increased in recent years, especially for women of the younger generations who want to be mothers. mothers.
is what the study "and professional career women in Spain," conducted by the CSIC in collaboration with the Instituto de la Mujer..
The survey, conducted on 9 737 women aged 15 to 75 years, leaves no room for doubt: 75% of working mothers saw their professional career limited because of motherhood.
The study indicates that there are many differences concerning the beginning of life as a couple and the number of children, whether or not the woman works or not, and the type of job. job.
Those who do not work outside the home, working part-time or have a stable, earlier in the couple, have their first pregnancy earlier and have more children. children.
In contrast, women with a stable job, mainly in the public sector, the entry in the life as a couple and the first pregnancy, and have fewer children.
Women aged between 35 and 49 years with a fixed work have their first child, on average, 3.7 years after being installed as a couple. This figure rises to among those who work in the public sector. "These data show that women with a stable employment needed more time in their lives for it, which led to the union and the arrival of children. of
In addition, the type of employment exercised influence, but less than the start date of common life together, "said the researcher of the Margarita Delgado..
The level of education is another factor that is widening the gap in the age of marriage for women and their first child.
According to the survey, the higher the level of training is high, the more they marry and have their first child later.
The difference is also among the women of the same generation.
For example, in the group aged between 35 and 49 years, those who have elementary and higher, respectively mothers for the first time to and years on average..
"Another disctinction is also between women, according to their level of education.
While those who have elementary school marry and have their first child before finding a stable job, those with average level or higher this program and give priority to obtaining a stable work as a precondition to marriage and the arrival of a child, "said Ms. Delgado.. Ms. Delgado.
