Michelin and Fesvial, sets for
The tyre manufacturer Michelin, in collaboration with the for the Road Safety Foundation (Fesvial), has launched a campaign to encourage the wearing of the helmet, mainly among the younger, as reported today the two structures..
This initiative aims to raise awareness of the importance of the, since it is the only element of protection to avoid injuries to the head, or even death, in the event of an accident in two wheels..
Michelin said that the campaign was in line with his commitment to road safety, "which goes beyond the design and manufacture of products always safer" and said that it contributed to this objective by other actions to educational and informative..
This new campaign to encourage of the two wheels, under the motto "To be or not to be," will include a first phase, during which posters will be distributed in more than 500 garages of motorcycles, in order to ensure the widest possible dissemination.
Finally, Michelin has stressed that road safety "is a constant concern" for the company, because as a manufacturer of tyres for two-wheeled vehicles, one of its main objectives is to develop products always safer..
The sale of light commercial vehicles is
After almost two years, the market for light commercial vehicles are beginning to see a little light at the end of the tunnel..
The 9 425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decline, according to figures from the employers' union of and Ganvam, the number of dealers.
, however, the good news, since the reference for the comparison, the month of November 2008, has been particularly bad, with a decrease of 60% decrease compared to the previous year.
, despite the rebound last month, the accumulated during the 11 months are 40% below those of the previous year.
Since January, if you add up all vehicles entering into the category of light commercial vehicles (derived from passenger cars, light trucks, vans, and chassis) 95 have been sold.
clouds that most affect their are not so. Indeed, although they are also purchased by individuals, most of the purchases are made by small or medium-sized businesses, which pay in almost 100% of cases through an external funding..
Thus, in addition to the restrictions by the limitation of bank loans, other factors such as the increase in the unemployment rate or the persistence of the poor economic climate..
Faced with this situation and the passenger vehicles, aid for the purchase of the 2000E have little used...
In addition to individuals, the self-employed and to acquire a light commercial vehicle of less than 3.5 tonnes with a level of emissions of does not exceed 160 grams per kilometre, can also benefit, but the number of operations speaks for itself.
