A fine of $63 million to France Telecom to curb competition
The French competition regulator imposed a fine of EUR 63 million euros to France Telecom for its anti-competitive conduct in the Caribbean region in the country..
According to this institution, the operator has limited competition in the fixed and mobile telephony by signing exclusive agreements, tariffs and loyalty programs to consumers on the of the regulation.
With this sanction, the former French monopoly and even state, accumulating more than 450 million euros in fines since 1994, because of the obstacles it puts its competitors.
The yesterday has been increased because the authority which oversees competition considers that France Telecom has committed similar offences in the past and that it is therefore repeat offender.
