The Champions League has become a source of income for clubs, since its birth in 1992.
Indeed, Real Madrid and FC Barcelona have won 467,4 million, which puts them in third and fifth position of clubs who have pocketed the most money in this competition..
The Manchester United is at the top of the list.
The Manchester United is at the top of the list.
Win the UEFA Champions League does not only the glory. It is also one of the main sources of income of big clubs..
Indeed, the competition has allocated 5 million euros to 105 teams (including 12) who participated in the event since the creation of the tournament, during the season, according to the information from UEFA.
The Real Madrid and FC Barcelona have been well served in this distribution.
