This apparent paradox is explained by the complex procedure of allocation of money applied by UEFA.
For this year, the body chaired by Michel Platini expects to earn 1 million through to the Champions League.
Of this amount, UEFA will 413,1 million fixed payments: each of the 20 clubs who participated in the classification matches (including the Atlético Madrid) received 2.1 million.
In addition, those who have managed to participate received 3.8 million just to be there, in addition to 550 euros for each match..
There is also a bonus in the event of victory (800 000 euros) and equality (400 000 for each team). Those who arrive in of receive three million each, the eight teams who arrive in the quarter-final reçoivent3,3 million..
The last four teams will each receive 4 million.
And the champion will win $9 million, to the received by the other finalist..
