Internet auction of cars
Last October, the group has Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars, motorcycles and special vehicles.
The operation has involved a cost of 59.5 million euros for 85% of the company's capital, which could next year to the remaining 15%.
The purpose of the acquisition was to provide more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of access to a huge international market.
This service and sale is intended exclusively for professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, leasing companies, garages, and sellers who must be registered before starting to carry out operations..
This platform was created in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650 000 operations across Europe, including in Germany..
Among its major markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
There are currently more than sellers and experts registered on the site.
It manages ads per day and on the Spanish market, 100 new announcements are published every day.
